    "divine_council_note": "1 Enoch 55 explicitly involves the angelic administration of natural order. [C] The text describes angels assigned to manage the waters, ensuring they remain within their appointed bounds. [B] This reflects the broader biblical theme that God governs creation through delegated authority — the 'host of heaven' (tsava hashamayim) execute his decrees (Psalm 103:20–21, 148:2–6). [A] The rainbow covenant in Genesis 9:13 is a 'sign between me and the earth' — a visible reminder to God himself, suggesting covenant memory is institutionalized in the created order. [C] In Enochic cosmology, this institutionalization occurs through angelic overseers who maintain the boundaries God established. The oath sworn in 1 Enoch 55 binds not only God but the entire cosmic hierarchy to uphold the post-diluvian order.",
    
